Forgot these?

They also have % hp or % missing hp damage.

Items that give health as the only defensive stat:

{{item:3107}} {{item:3309}} {{item:2065}}
{{item:3027}} {{item:3116}}{{item:3151}} {{item:3152}} 
{{item:3053}} {{item:3071}} {{item:3748}}{{item:3078}} 
{{item:3083}} 

Interestingly enough, Warmongs is the only one actually meant for tanks. 

{{item:3143}}  is not going to be as effective since crits are generally going to be doing 50% less damage, and 20% of their damage will be un-reduceable true damage.

{{item:3024}} items are probably going to be far less useful, since they often come with minimal to no health and the armor is going to be less effective across the board with the new IE and LW.

{{item:3193}} is still going to be useful because of the active though. I wouldn't be surprised to start seeing {{item:3193}} {{item:3047}} as the only items I actually take for the armor on a tank, with the rest being a MR+HP ({{item:3001}}{{item:3065}} {{item:3194}}) and HP+damage ({{item:3071}} {{item:3027}} {{item:3053}}) because the best defense is to kill them first.

{{item:3110}} 

How about this, then? Guaranteed 15% DPS cut (crit doesn't matter), 100 Armor, 20% CdR.

Get a health item to pair with it and you should be gucci.
